OL,3,CDame Jenni Murray, former BBC
OL,4,Cpresenter, dies aged 75
OL,6,FDame Jenni Murray, who hosted BBC
OL,7,FRadio 4's Woman's Hour for more than
OL,8,Fthree decades, has died aged 75, the
OL,9,FBBC has said.
OL,11,FShe became the longest-serving host in
OL,12,Fthe BBC Radio 4 programme's history
OL,13,Fbefore leaving in 2020, having first
OL,14,Fappeared on the broadcast in 1987.
OL,16,FA statement shared by her family to
OL,17,FThe Daily Mail confirmed "the very sad
OL,18,Fnews that their much loved mum and
OL,19,Fwife, Jenni Murray, died on March
OL,20,F12th".
