OL,3,CDame Jenni Murray, former BBC
OL,4,Cpresenter, dies aged 75
OL,6,FBBC director-general Tim Davie paid
OL,7,Ftribute to the broadcaster, writing:
OL,8,F"Her legacy endures in the countless
OL,9,Fconversations she started, the many
OL,10,Fissues she championed and the lives
OL,11,Fshe touched."
OL,13,FMohit Bakaya, controller of BBC Radio
OL,14,F4 and director of BBC speech audio,
OL,15,Fdescribed Dame Jenni as "a formidable
OL,16,Fvoice in British broadcasting".
